text: Antonio Maria Priuli (1707–1772) was a Roman Catholic cardinal who served as Cardinal-Priest of San Marco (1762–1772), Bishop of Padova (1767–1772), Cardinal-Priest of Santa Maria della Pace (1759–1762), and Bishop of Vicenza (1738–1767). ==References== ==External links and additional sources== * (for Chronology of Bishops) * (for Chronology of Bishops) * (for Chronology of Bishops) * (for Chronology of Bishops) Category:18th-century Roman Catholic bishops Category:1707 births Category:1772 deaths
